FBIS3-60863 "jptot001__l94111" JPRS-TOT-94-001-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 7 January 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA RUSSIA Four Caucasians Kidnap Children; No Motive Given Hijackers Have `Explosive Device' LD2612112793 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1046 GMT 26 Dec 93 LD2612112793 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Nikolay Styazhkin] [Excerpt] Mineralnyye Vody, Stavropol Territory, December 26 TASS -- [passage omitted] The operations headquarters which maintains contact with the gunmen has information that the two boys and three adult hostages feel satisfactorily. The Mineralnyye Vody airport services regularly deliver meals to those on board. One still has to approach the helicopter at gunpoint. The suppositions that the gunmen have a high-powered explosive device have been confirmed. [passage omitted]
